# Reflection: Coding My CV Using Markdown 

## Situation
As part of the Project Presentation 3 assessment, I was required to code my CV
using Markdown and publish it on GitHub.

## Task
My task was to learn GitHub Flavoured Markdown and use it to create a
well-structured, professional CV that is suitable for industry viewing.

## Action
I researched Markdown syntax and i watched Youtube videos trying to learn and understand this language, including headings, lists, links, and formatting.
I then converted my traditional CV into Markdown format and structured it
clearly using sections such as education, skills, and projects that I have done.

## Result
I successfully created a clean and professional CV using Markdown.
This improved my technical documentation skills and helped me understand
how developers present information in a clear and readable way.
